Jirau Plant in Brazil May Be Delayed on Unrest, Estado Says

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-03-18T12:47:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/jirau-plant-in-brazil-may-be-delayed-on-unrest-estado-says.html
Construction of the Jirau
hydroelectric plant in  Brazil  may get delayed after workers
destroyed and set fire to installations at the construction
site, Victor Paranhos, the head of the project, told the  O
Estado de S. Paulo  newspaper.  Police have intervened to control the unrest, the paper
said. The group building Jirau includes GDF Suez, Camargo Correa
and Centrais Electricas Brasileiras SA, the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Millard in  Rio de Janeiro  at 
 Pmillard1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  